====================================================\
1. SYSTEM PHILOSOPHY\
====================================================\
\
This system is not a simple website.\
\
This system is a Content-Driven Conversion Platform.\
\
This system is a Growth System.\
\
This system must support:\
\
- Trust-based lead generation\
- Dynamic CMS content\
- Admin-managed website structure\
- Multilingual content\
- RTL and LTR rendering\
- Lead capture\
- Lead management\
- Theme management\
- CTA management\
- Grade funnel management\
- SEO management\
- Media management\
- Audit logging\
- Content versioning\
- Future commerce expansion\
- Future customer portal expansion\
- Future parent portal expansion\
- Future student portal expansion\
\
The system must allow non-developers to manage all website content without breaking the user experience.\
\
No public-facing business content may be hardcoded in frontend components.\
\
====================================================\
2. CORE ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLES\
====================================================\
\
The architecture is divided into four primary layers:\
\
1. Presentation Layer\
\
2. Service Layer\
\
3. Content and Business Logic Layer\
\
4. Database Layer\
\
----------------------------------------------------\
2.1 PRESENTATION LAYER\
----------------------------------------------------\
\
The Presentation Layer includes:\
\
- Public website pages\
- Homepage\
- Contact page\
- Service detail pages\
- Case study detail pages\
- Team profile pages\
- Event detail pages\
- Admin panel UI\
- CMS interfaces\
- Form interfaces\
- Media interfaces\
- Future portal interfaces\
- Future commerce interfaces\
\
Rules:\
\
- Presentation components must not query Prisma directly.\
- Presentation components must not contain hardcoded business content.\
- Presentation components must receive validated DTOs.\
- Presentation components must support RTL and LTR.\
- Presentation components must follow the UI Design System.\
- Public homepage section order must remain aligned with the Wireframe Specification.\
\
----------------------------------------------------\
2.2 SERVICE LAYER\
----------------------------------------------------\
\
The Service Layer is responsible for:\
\
- Data fetching\
- DTO transformation\
- Business logic\
- Permission checks\
- Validation coordination\
- Cache invalidation\
- Content publishing actions\
- Lead processing\
- Media processing\
- Theme resolution\
- CTA resolution\
- Grade funnel resolution\
\
All public rendering must follow this flow:\
\
Database\
\uc0\u8594  Service Layer\
\uc0\u8594  DTO Validation\
\uc0\u8594  React Server Component\
\uc0\u8594  Renderer\
\
Direct database access inside visual components is prohibited.\
\
----------------------------------------------------\
2.3 CONTENT AND BUSINESS LOGIC LAYER\
----------------------------------------------------\
\
This layer includes:\
\
- CMS content rules\
- Homepage section order rules\
- CTA behavior rules\
- Grade funnel behavior\
- Lead lifecycle rules\
- Content lifecycle rules\
- SEO rules\
- Admin permissions\
- Audit log rules\
- Versioning rules\
\
The business logic layer must prevent Admin users from accidentally breaking the trust-based conversion flow.\
\
----------------------------------------------------\
2.4 DATABASE LAYER\
----------------------------------------------------\
\
The Database Layer must provide:\
\
- PostgreSQL storage\
- Prisma ORM schema\
- Strict relational integrity\
- UUID primary keys\
- Dedicated bilingual fields\
- Explicit relations\
- Audit logs\
- Content version snapshots\
- Future commerce readiness\
- Future portal readiness\
\
====================================================\
3. MULTILINGUAL CONTENT RULE\
====================================================\
\
Primary editable content must always use dedicated bilingual fields.\
\
Allowed primary content pattern:\
\
title_en\
\
title_fa\
\
headline_en\
\
headline_fa\
\
description_en\
\
description_fa\
\
content_en\
\
content_fa\
\
cta_label_en\
\
cta_label_fa\
\
alt_text_en\
\
alt_text_fa\
\
meta_title_en\
\
meta_title_fa\
\
meta_description_en\
\
meta_description_fa\
\
JSON blobs are prohibited for primary editable content.\
\
JSON fields are allowed only for:\
\
- metadata\
- social links\
- campaign data\
- audit snapshots\
- technical configuration\
- analytics configuration\
- optional structured settings\
- non-primary flexible data\
\
JSON fields are prohibited for:\
\
- titles\
- headlines\
- descriptions\
- body content\
- CTA labels\
- SEO titles\
- SEO descriptions\
- primary localized website content\
\
====================================================\
4. DATABASE ENGINE AND ORM\
====================================================\
\
Database Engine:\
\
PostgreSQL\
\
ORM:\
\
Prisma ORM\
\
Required Database Principles:\
\
- UUID primary keys\
- Strict relational integrity\
- Explicit relations\
- Dedicated bilingual fields\
- Soft delete where appropriate\
- Audit trail for admin actions\
- Version snapshots for important content updates\
- CMS-friendly data structures\
- Future-safe expansion model\
\
====================================================\
5. PRISMA SCHEMA CONTRACT\
====================================================\
\
The final implementation must include a complete working Prisma schema.\
\
The schema must not be documentation-only.\
\
It must be capable of passing:\
\
npx prisma generate\
\
npx prisma migrate dev\
\
npx prisma db seed\
\
without errors.\
\
